  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Development and Conservation in the Upper Area of the Cahabon River Watershed</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Indigenous Q&#xB4;eqchies who live near the ridge of the Cahabon river watershed in Alta Verapaz department of Guatemala are under employed, have few labor alternatives, are plagued by illiteracy and have no access to potable water, draining systems and electricity. The region, rich in natural resources, is threatened by deforestation, which affects water sources that supply 10,000 families. The main goal of this project is to promote activities that will provide income and conserve the biodiversity and natural resources in the region for 800 families. The project will distribute 180 rabbits, 252 turkeys, 81 sheep and 3,600 earthworms. Training also will be provided in natural and environmental history, and in activities that will conserve the natural resources and improve habitat.</narrative>
  </description>
